      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AT THE GATE (8) goes very well here starting 12 times for five wins and five minors. Comes off a (23.09) win last time, scoring by 0.8 lengths in a Grade 5 over 400m at The Gardens. Looks suited here and rates on top. AL CAN DO (6) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by a nose at this track in a handy 17.54 beating Watch Her Win. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from six starts. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. SEE RED (4) doesn't win out of turn but recent form sound. Filled a minor placings again last time when third (17.52) at this track making it three placings in a row. Has a good record at this journey. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Deserves a win and gets her chance. MARRA LAD (1) with some luck can improve on an unplaced run last time here.",
